postcontent: Factory new, unfired, Remington Model 870 Police Magnum shotgun, chambered for both 2&3/4 and 3 Magnum 12 gauge shells. This is the variant with the adjustable rifle sights. This shotgun is brand new in box, with all factory paperwork. Remington's 870 is a legendary pump action shotgun today that needs no introduction. It has served sportsman, law enforcement, and even the military alike for over half a century. It is simply put, one of the best shotgun designs of all time, with a track record for reliability and durability. The Police Magnum 870 variant takes an already great firearm, and insures it is even better. Remington builds these in a special section of its factory with only skilled workers doing the assembly. Each individual part is inspected before it is used, and each completed weapon goes through a 23 point QC process before going out the door. The 870P is built on a forged steel receiver, which is smoothed of any inperfections before assembly. Both the extractor and ejector are also made of forged steel, to insure they will have long service lives. Extra power springs are used in the magazine tube, carrier, and trigger group. In otherwords, although the Police Magnum isn't cheap, Remington cuts no corners during the entire manufacturing process. After all, these shotguns are intended for use by law enforcement officers, who could one day depend on their shotgun to save their lives or the lives of others. This shotgun 100% new, factory fresh, and in its original serial matched factory box. It has a factory part SKU# of 24401. The receiver is marked Police Magnum, the barrel is 20" long with an improved cylinder bore, and the trigger guard is made of metal (not polymer). Other features include factory adjustable rifle sights, standard 4+1 tube (will accept a +2 extension without any modifications), and front sling swivel stud. All of the metal parts have a factory milspec type parkerized finish, which is extremely rust resistant. This is a Remington 870 Police Magnum in a modern tactical configuration, assembled with quality partsWE Have just received some brand new in the box Remington 870 Police Magnums, 20" IC barrel with rifle sight. RMA's Level IV (model #1189) single-curve ballistic rifle plates are designed to withstand rugged usage while not compromising the ballistic integrity of the plate. The Level IV is NIJ Certified multi-hit .30-06 M2AP tested by an NIJ certified laboratory and can defeat between 5-7 M2AP rounds.

RMA has no hesitation in claiming that their level IV rifle plate is the strongest of its kind on the market today. The reasoning is simple: RMA uses a patented ceramic tile array to greatly reduce crack propagation. Conventional level IV plates use a monolithic piece of ceramic, which, when hit by an M2AP round, produces 'spiderweb' cracks across the plate, greatly reducing the plate's ability to defeat multiple rounds.

RMA's patented tile array essentially tells the ceramic where to crack upon impact, mitigating the damage and integrity to the rest of the plate and ensuring full protection to armor piercing rounds on other parts of the ceramic.

This patented process undeniably provides world-class safety to military and law enforcement personnel across the globe that is unmatched by any other manufacturer.

This pistol, unlike ANY other handgun, has the barrel precisely at the level of the index finger. As a result, there is no rotation of the gun after the cartridge is fired but BEFORE the bullet leaves the barrel.   It can fire any velocity .22lr ammunition. The muzzle brake can be removed, but is essential for high accuracy with supersonic .22lr ammunition. The weight system is used to tune the gun and remove unwanted harmonic vibration. If the weights are not used, the gun does tend to develop a bi or trimodal impact point. However, these pistols usually have a 0.15 MOA accuracy at 50 meters. The firing mechanism, surprising perhaps, derives from the one used in the SAKO Finnmaster, but the gun has many advantages over the SAKO.  The bar also helps in aligning the gun vertically. That noted, this is perhaps the only gun that is designed to be fired in ANY POSITION or degree of cant or rotation. That includes inverted, or the ridiculous "on its side" position used in lots of movies and TV shows now. title: For Sale:  MII 715T FT 22LR Mossberg International
postcontent:
The .22LR mossberg 715t is a great gun if you are looking for something that is reliable and very reasonably priced. It looks like an AR15 but it is lighter and of course much cheaper and lighter at around 5.2 pounds. The Mossberg tactical 22 is light enough to carry around but still holds enough shooting power to take down just about any animal up to a coyote. It is a great choice for anyone looking for a fun tactical .22LR for only around $250-$300.

There are two main models with an additional two other variations. The Mossberg 715T flat top and the 715T tactical carry handle. They all have the great M4 adjustable stock and fit the 10 or 25 round magazines. The 715T carry handle is not only the handle but it is also where the rear sight is located and of course is where you place your optics. The carry handle version does not have muzzlebrake. The one up for sale is a flat top.


See http://mossberg715t.com/
